{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Cslib/Computability/URM/Computable.html#Cslib.URM.Computable\"><span class=\"name\">Cslib</span>.<span class=\"name\">URM</span>.<span class=\"name\">Computable</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Part.html#Part\">Part</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A partial function `f : (Fin n → ℕ) → Part ℕ` is URM-computable if there exists a URM program\nthat computes it. ","docLink":"./Cslib/Computability/URM/Computable.html#Cslib.URM.Computable","kind":"def","line":38,"name":"Cslib.URM.Computable","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/b00648a4fe741981bb586a3cc845258ab1583f61/Cslib/Computability/URM/Computable.lean#L38-L41"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Cslib/Computability/URM/Computable.html#Cslib.URM.Computes\"><span class=\"name\">Cslib</span>.<span class=\"name\">URM</span>.<span class=\"name\">Computes</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/URM/Defs.html#Cslib.URM.Program\">Program</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Part.html#Part\">Part</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A program `p` computes a partial function `f : (Fin n → ℕ) → Part ℕ` if for any input,\n`eval p inputs = f inputs` as partial values. This captures both:\n- The program halts iff the function is defined on that input\n- When both are defined, the program's output equals the function's value\n\nNote: Inputs are provided in registers 0, 1, ..., n-1 and output is read from register 0. ","docLink":"./Cslib/Computability/URM/Computable.html#Cslib.URM.Computes","kind":"def","line":29,"name":"Cslib.URM.Computes","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/b00648a4fe741981bb586a3cc845258ab1583f61/Cslib/Computability/URM/Computable.lean#L29-L36"}}],"imports":["Init","Cslib.Computability.URM.Execution"],"instances":[],"name":"Cslib.Computability.URM.Computable"}